</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Speaking of BlackRock Inc. saving the =
world on your behalf, BlackRock Chief Executive Officer Larry Fink said rec=
ently about its ESG efforts=C2=A0that=C2=A0=E2=80=9CBlackRock is a leader i=
n this, and we are seeing the flows, and I continue to see this big shift i=
n investor portfolios.=E2=80=9D But <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/26253475.277659/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTItMzEvaG93LWJsYWNrcm9jay1zLWludmlzaWJsZS1oYW5kLWhlbHBl=
ZC1tYWtlLWVzZy1hLWhvdC10aWNrZXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEwNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21=
lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMTA0JnV0bV9jYW=
1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3fbab451" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Bloomber=
g News=C2=A0notes</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What Fin=
k did not say is that BlackRock drove a significant part of that shift by i=
nserting its primary ESG fund into popular and influential model portfolios=
 offered to investment advisers, who use them with clients across North Ame=
rica. The huge flows from such models mean many investors got into an ESG v=
ehicle without necessarily choosing one as a specific investment strategy, =
or even knowing that their money has gone into one.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">In short, an apparent BlackRock-led rush of investors into ESG in =
the past two years has been something of a self-fulfilling prophecy, at lea=
st when it comes to the biggest such fund on the planet, a BlackRock exchan=
ge-traded fund that trades under the ticker symbol ESGU, according to data =
from BlackRock and Morningstar. ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Jan.=
 15, 2020, the day after Fink=E2=80=99s letter predicted a major reallocati=
on of capital into sustainability, BlackRock altered its most popular suite=
 of model portfolios by adding ESGU into its =E2=80=9CTarget Allocation ETF=
 Portfolio Strategies=E2=80=9D series. (The biggest and most popular one in=
side the suite, which offers a 60/40 split between stocks and fixed income =
investments, includes ESGU as one of its top two holdings.)</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">In this way, BlackRock itself helped assure Fink=E2=80=99s=
 prediction would come true. Financial planners who use the models through =
online platforms have had no choice but to put their clients in ESGU if the=
y wanted to get them into one of the most popular investment strategies for=
 sale.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This seems =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0obviously good? The problem, for BlackRock, is that it is largely in the=
 business of selling index funds. It has a big S&amp;P 500 index fund, and =
if a stock is in the S&amp;P 500 index then BlackRock has to own that stock=
, and if that stock is a coal company then, you know, oops. BlackRock can g=
o to the coal company and say =E2=80=9Cwe are a 5% shareholder of your comp=
any and we want you to mine less coal,=E2=80=9D but (1) that is pretty self=
-defeating and (2) if the company says no, what can BlackRock=C2=A0do,=C2=
=A0sell its stock? And so Larry Fink sends out letters about how companies =
should do better at ESG, but his funds mostly don=E2=80=99t get to pick wha=
t stocks they buy, so they end up owning lots of stocks that are bad at ESG=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Fink does get to pick, within limits,=
=C2=A0<em>what funds his investors buy</em>. If you change the model portfo=
lio=E2=80=99s main stock allocation from the S&amp;P 500 to an ESG fund, an=
d your clients blithely go along, then you will find yourself buying more g=
ood ESG stocks and fewer bad ESG stocks while still basically offering inde=
x funds. As a <em>fund manager</em>=C2=A0you are largely passive, but as a=
=C2=A0<em>marketer of funds=C2=A0</em>you get to do quite a lot of active a=
llocation. The people buying your passive funds are not, after all, deeply =
engaged connoisseurs of the stock market; they=E2=80=99re buying a model po=
rtfolio of passive BlackRock funds because they don't want to think too har=
d about stocks. Might as well put the stocks=C2=A0you like in there!</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When BlackRock first announced its plans to do th=
is back in 2020, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
6253475.277659/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
